import LegalPage from "~/components/LegalPage.astro";
---

<LegalPage locale="en" title="Privacy policy" lastUpdated="2026-05-20" path="/legal/privacy">
  <p>
    Keyfount is designed to collect nothing. This policy describes the
    data the extension and the website handle, why, and where it goes — which,
    by design, is nowhere.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data we collect</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>None.</strong> The extension and the website do not transmit your
    master password, derived passwords, email address, site domains, per-site
    configuration, IP address, browsing history, telemetry, crash reports, or
    any other personal data to the Project or to any third party.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data stored locally on your device</h2>
  <p>
    The extension stores the following data inside your browser's local
    extension storage, on your device only:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Per-site derivation profiles (length, character classes, counter, suffix rules). Metadata only — never the derived password itself.</li>
    <li>Your interface preferences (theme, language).</li>
    <li>An optional, locally-encrypted hint for your master password if you choose to set one.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This data never leaves your device. You can inspect and erase it at any
    time from the extension settings or from the browser's extension storage
    inspector.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Cookies and trackers</h2>
  <p>
    The website does not set cookies and does not embed any third-party
    analytics, advertising, fingerprinting, or social-media tracker. Open your
    browser's network inspector while using the site to verify: no requests
    leave your machine after the initial page load.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Permissions requested by the extension</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>storage</strong> — to persist per-site derivation profiles
      locally on your device.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>activeTab</strong> — to read the current tab's URL when you
      explicitly invoke the extension, so it can suggest the right
      per-site profile. The URL is processed in memory only and never
      stored or transmitted.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>scripting</strong> — to fill the focused password field when
      you click "fill". The script reads no other data from the page.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The extension does not request network permissions and cannot reach the
    network from its content scripts.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    The Service is not directed at children under 13. Because the Service
    collects no data, no specific children's data is ever processed.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Because no personal data leaves your device, there is no data on our side
    to access, correct, or erase. Under the GDPR and similar laws, your rights
    of access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, and objection
    apply to the local data stored by the extension — which you control
    directly through the extension settings.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    Material changes to this policy will be reflected by updating the "Last
    updated" date above and, where appropriate, by an in-extension notice on
    the next update.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For any privacy question, open an issue on the project repository at <a
      href="https://github.com/Keyfount"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/Keyfount</a
    >.
  </p>
</LegalPage>
